benak.tomas.crimemonitor.library

Interface UtvarAndIntervalBasedCrimeSummary

  • All Superinterfaces:
    UtvarBasedCrimeSummary
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CrimesList, CrimesSummary, CrimesSummaryBasic, CrimeSummaryDetailed, CrimeSummaryWithUtvarAndIntervalBase, CrimeUtvarDetail

    public interface UtvarAndIntervalBasedCrimeSummary
extends UtvarBasedCrimeSummary
    A base interface for providing a crime data interval context.

    To an implementing class, this interface adds the ability to associate the crime statistics with a particular crime data interval.

    When crime statistics get associated with the crime data interval, it means that all of the crimes that are used to create those statistics, have been committed during the crime data interval.

    The crime data interval is an interval starting with a given month in a given year and ending with another month in another year.

    Author:
    Tom
